<h2 id="preparation">Preparation</h2>

<p>Here are the steps to cook the meal. Takes as long as it takes. Share and enjoy!</p>

<ol>
  <li>Play music in the kitchen. <a href="https://open.spotify.com/playlist/37i9dQZF1DX1riuLHc7Ui5?si=P7Fz8s18QQKamfbkYGBJ_w">I recommend this playlist.</a></li>
  <li>Pore a glass of drink for the chef.</li>
  <li>Chop up the onions finely and chuck it in a frying pan. Add the lard and the speck if available. Start frying.</li>
  <li>When the onions have gone soft, add the paprika and load the pork shoulders on it. Keep stirring.</li>
  <li>add a glass of water, and sprinkle 2 pinches of vegetable mix over the stew.</li>
  <li>Let the pork soften under the lid for about 25 minutes, and top up the water gradually. season with pepper and salt.</li>
  <li>Meantime, slice up the potato and add it to the stew after 25 minutes. Add enough water such that it covers the potato. Cook them together until the potato goes soft.</li>
  <li>grate the garlic onto the stew, just before turning the hob off.</li>
  <li>Serve it with pickles, e.g. gherkins.</li>
</ol>
